Package: shinyCTT
Type: Package
Title: Easy to use analysis tools for psychometric tests in the CTT framework
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("R. Maximilian", "Bee", email = "r.maximilian.bee@fu-berlin.de",
    role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Michael", "Eid", email = "michael.eid@fu-berlin.de",
    role = "aut"))
URL: https://github.com/abeeisnotabug/shinyCTT
BugReports: https://github.com/abeeisnotabug/shinyCTT/issues
Description: The package provides a Shiny App to analyze datasets in the
    framework of classical test theory based on the lavaan package. Most
    importantly, the model assumptions of the 5 CTT models are checked in
    decreasing order of complexity (tau-kongeneric, essentially tau-equivalent,
    tau-equivalent and essentially tau-parallel, and tau-parallel) and the
    reliability estimators are adjusted accordingly. Moreover, it provides
    standard errors and confidence intervals for all parameters, including
    item reliabilities and error variances.
